15.plot: Beatriz takes refuge at Vicente's House and confesses him that she wants to divorce Joaquim, but Joaquim finds her and brings her home, forcing her to tell that it was her own decision. Alexa is hired at the Sherazade and meets Luz there who tells her that she was kidnapped by Tiburòn. She decides to help her escaping. After escaping, Duarte finds her running on the road and helps her, without knowing she's her daughter. Tiburòn pursues them but the police stops him and he loses sight of them. imdb.plot outline: Luz (which birth name is Benedita) was abandoned in a river by her stepmother when she was a baby, and was found by a couple of gypsies who adopted her. Nobody ever knew her stepmother abandoned her, not even her husband. 20 years later, she lives with her adoptive father in Mexico and doesn't know she was adopted, while her real father tries everything to find her; He will go to Mexico after receiving information about a woman who can help him finding Luz, and will even meet her several times in Mexico and in Portugal as well, without even knowing that she's his daughter. Luz's return to Portugal will cause a sequel of twists and turns and many conflicts with those who are against her as well.
